After some IRC chat with [~dmitrii], the following information may be helpful:

{code}
virsh dumpxml
{code}

then
{code}
tail -f http_nc-error.log
{code}

to check how frequently the errors are printed. The interval of time between the prints, could tell us which one of the thread is triggering this warning.  And finally

{code}
pstack <pid>
{code}

where the <pid> is  the process ID of the eucalyptus-nc process owned by eucalyptus user.

Hi Ben,

I think, it should be run on NC.

{{ps aux | grep httpd}}
{{pstack <pid>}}
